in carolus stuardus ( 1657 ) he dramatised events of his own day , namely the death of king charles i of england ; his other tragedies are leo armenius ( 1650 ) ; catharina von georgien ( 1657 ) , cardenio und celinde ( 1657 ) and papinianus ( 1659 ) .

17th century drama : " carolus stuardus " by andreas gryphius is about this executed king of england

charles i